Are you kidding? He forgot the time.

805
00:51:33,890 --> 00:51:35,152
Everyone's here.

806
00:51:37,327 --> 00:51:39,318
Not only. Look at the third row.

807
00:51:39,529 --> 00:51:41,963
The cream of the press is here.

808
00:51:42,132 --> 00:51:43,759
Even the radio has come.

809
00:51:44,134 --> 00:51:47,297
- Here we go. Mazel tov!
- Don't screw up.

810
00:51:47,471 --> 00:51:48,836
Showtime!

811
00:51:51,074 --> 00:51:53,474
Good evening.
Welcome to the Chansonia.

812
00:51:53,643 --> 00:51:56,305
It's an important evening
for our music hall...

813
00:51:56,480 --> 00:51:57,469
Break a leg!

814
00:51:57,647 --> 00:51:58,978
...run by Mr. Pigoil.

815
00:51:59,149 --> 00:52:00,673
Over to you.

816
00:52:00,851 --> 00:52:02,409
Show them what we're made of.

817
00:52:02,586 --> 00:52:05,680
Remember what I said, keep smiling.

818
00:52:06,089 --> 00:52:07,886
Your paper!

819
00:52:10,694 --> 00:52:12,457
Ready?

820
00:52:13,563 --> 00:52:14,965
Here we go.

821
00:52:34,951 --> 00:52:35,940
Go on.

822
00:52:37,287 --> 00:52:40,222
Good evening
and welcome to the Chansonia...

823
00:52:40,757 --> 00:52:42,782
...for its gala reopening.

824
00:52:42,993 --> 00:52:46,258
This is a big night for our music hall...

825
00:52:46,429 --> 00:52:48,420
...now run by Mr. Pigoil...

826
00:52:53,036 --> 00:52:54,264
...and his friends.

827
00:52:54,437 --> 00:52:56,132
Strip!

828
00:52:57,941 --> 00:52:58,999
Only after you do.

829
00:53:04,447 --> 00:53:08,679
We wouldn't be here
without everyone who believed in us.

830
00:53:10,220 --> 00:53:13,951
For fresh produce every day
One address, chez Crouzet

831
00:53:17,594 --> 00:53:20,256
For his cooking and fine wine

832
00:53:20,430 --> 00:53:23,058
Take a table at Célestin's

833
00:53:26,770 --> 00:53:30,365
And thank you to Mr. Galapiat
who made this possible.

834
00:53:31,775 --> 00:53:33,242
No need to overdo it.

835
00:53:33,410 --> 00:53:34,434
And now...

836
00:53:34,611 --> 00:53:37,478
...the man known
as "The Prince of lmitators."

837
00:53:37,948 --> 00:53:40,109
Yes, the one and only...

838
00:53:40,283 --> 00:53:41,750
...Jacky Jacquet!

839
00:53:47,791 --> 00:53:48,780
Perfect!

840
00:53:48,959 --> 00:53:50,927
- Really?
- lf the manager says so...

841
00:53:51,094 --> 00:53:53,460
Get the next announcement ready.

842
00:53:53,630 --> 00:53:55,962
Jacky, we're right behind you.

843
00:54:08,645 --> 00:54:10,010
Bravo, Jacky!

844
00:54:16,453 --> 00:54:17,818
Thank you.

845
00:54:18,154 --> 00:54:21,521
Thanks to Jacky,
the Prince of lmitators...

846
00:54:21,691 --> 00:54:23,181
...we're taking flight.

847
00:54:23,360 --> 00:54:26,261
Here come the planes.

848
00:54:40,543 --> 00:54:44,377
You can picture the plane.
He's priceless.

849
00:54:50,220 --> 00:54:51,778
Thank you.

850
00:54:51,988 --> 00:54:54,513
Now let's go fishing.

851
00:54:54,691 --> 00:54:57,660
It's a sunny day.
Look up. What do I see there?

852
00:54:57,827 --> 00:55:01,319
Ducks!
Ducks, ladies and gentlemen.

853
00:55:03,667 --> 00:55:05,396
Do you see them?

854
00:55:05,568 --> 00:55:06,694
The daddy duck.

855
00:55:06,870 --> 00:55:07,859
The mommy duck.

856
00:55:08,071 --> 00:55:09,538
The ducklings.

857
00:55:11,374 --> 00:55:13,399
Ducks, ladies and gentlemen.

858
00:55:19,115 --> 00:55:21,606
We can't leave this fabulous place...

859
00:55:21,785 --> 00:55:23,514
...without hearing the frogs wake.

860
00:55:23,687 --> 00:55:25,382
Here come the frogs.

861
00:55:37,934 --> 00:55:41,335
It takes some doing.
He's alone up there.

862
00:55:41,638 --> 00:55:43,902
It's not easy.

863
00:55:44,107 --> 00:55:47,565
- He's not funny.
- Try doing the frog for this crowd.

864
00:55:47,744 --> 00:55:49,268
Thank you.

865
00:55:50,213 --> 00:55:51,202
Bravo!

866
00:55:57,420 --> 00:55:59,752
They're a bit cold tonight.

867
00:55:59,923 --> 00:56:02,118
I'll warm them up.

868
00:56:06,563 --> 00:56:08,292
You've been waiting for him.

869
00:56:08,465 --> 00:56:11,093
With special permission
from his sergeant- -

870
00:56:11,267 --> 00:56:12,393
A song!

871
00:56:12,569 --> 00:56:13,593
Yeah, a song!

872
00:56:13,937 --> 00:56:17,930
- - our greatest comic troupers.
You know who I mean, Poupart!

873
00:56:19,242 --> 00:56:21,142
A song!

874
00:56:22,312 --> 00:56:24,780
- What's wrong?
- She has to sing.

875
00:56:27,851 --> 00:56:28,977
- You have to sing.
- What?

876
00:56:29,152 --> 00:56:31,245
They want a song.
You must know one.

877
00:56:31,421 --> 00:56:32,479
No.

878
00:56:32,655 --> 00:56:34,646
- Not very well.
- lt'll do.

879
00:56:34,824 --> 00:56:36,416
- What about me?
- Later.

880
00:56:36,593 --> 00:56:38,458
Go on.

881
00:56:51,441 --> 00:56:53,306
It won't work.

882
00:56:57,580 --> 00:57:01,778
Whenever I'm far from Paris

883
00:57:01,951 --> 00:57:05,546
M\y lungs can't catch a breath

884
00:57:05,722 --> 00:57:09,556
M\y heart is filled with tears

885
00:57:09,726 --> 00:57:13,423
And my body feels exiled

886
00:57:13,596 --> 00:57:15,120
The furthest

887
00:57:15,298 --> 00:57:17,289
I ever went was along the M\arne

888
00:57:17,467 --> 00:57:21,096
To follow a little crush I had

889
00:57:21,271 --> 00:57:24,968
But as soon as all the din fades

890
00:57:25,141 --> 00:57:28,133
I'm bored for silence doesn't suit me

891
00:57:28,645 --> 00:57:31,273
Paris, Paris

892
00:57:32,549 --> 00:57:35,746
You're my only family

893
00:57:36,453 --> 00:57:39,513
Paris, Paris

894
00:57:40,190 --> 00:57:43,785
Only with you is my heart free

895
00:57:46,129 --> 00:57:49,462
If I don't see you again tomorrow

896
00:57:50,033 --> 00:57:52,934
Paris, I'll die

897
00:57:53,903 --> 00:57:56,838
Eaten up by sorrow

898
00:58:06,316 --> 00:58:10,013
You bewitch me with your charms

899
00:58:14,324 --> 00:58:17,851
I'll lie naked in your arms

900
00:58:20,063 --> 00:58:23,499
If I don't see you again tomorrow

901
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:27,261
Paris, I'll die

902
00:58:27,837 --> 00:58:34,868
Eaten up by sorrow

903
00:59:00,970 --> 00:59:01,959
You realize?

